headline: 1 Healthcare Stock Worth Investigating and 2 Facing Challenges
summary: From novel pharmaceuticals to telemedicine, most healthcare companies are on a mission to drive better patient outcomes. Despite the rosy long-term prospects, short-term headwinds such as COVID inventory destocking have harmed the industry’s returns - over the past six months, healthcare stocks have collectively shed 7.1%. This drawdown is a far cry from the S&P 500’s 4.7% ascent.
